<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Nyfeara on 02-21-2002 08:14 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Ok, after last night, decided to post about 2 of my experiences.

1- Met this druid in GF while shopping.  We are just acquaintances, never group together, say hello once in a while.  I'm preparing with a group to go into CoM & I get a tell from him asking if I can rez him in EJ.  Since I'm in EJ, I say sure, bring corpse to CoM zone.  He actually has 2 corpses.  About 15 min later the first one arrives.  He has trouble finding the 2nd one.  I tell him politely that I will rez the one that is here but my group is ready to head in & I'm not going to keep them waiting.  Rez done.  A couple weeks/month later, he sends me another tell from one of his alts.  Please come rez this alt before my corpse poofs.  His alt was like lev 15 or something & he was bound on another continent.  Unfortunately, I was already on the move with a group to our hunting spot.  I tell him I can't & he goes off a major tyrade about how everyone uses his druid character & refuses to help him.  Not once, have I ever received/asked for a port from this guy and being a 50+ druid, he should have gotten his alt bound a bit closer.

2- Just happened last night.  Was hunting in Ten Mts with 2 friends.  We have a guild hunt in Nurga later in the week.  We wrap things up & stop by in DL to drop off the ranger, then the druid & I are porting elsewhere to do our banking, etc & log for the evening.  No sooner do we land in DL, someone shoots me a tell asking me to rez him & 2 or 3 others out near KC.  I tell him, I'm sorry I can't - I'm just passing thru.  He tells me it will take only 3 mins, etc.  I tell him again, sorry I can't.  We port away.  Then I get multiple tells from the guy about how when he's high enough he will make sure that no group in Seb or any other zone will take me - he knows my name now & he has alts - then tell ME he's gonna put me on ignore.  Go figure - just a rude individual.

People like this frustrate you when you go out of your way to rez on a pretty regular basis.  /shrug



------------------
Nyfeara Panacea
Officer of the Blades of Light
50th Cleric of Tunare</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
